=============================================================
DSPLIB Version 1.1 - May 4, 2000
=============================================================

This software has been used in the experimental study of the
fully dynamic single-source shortest paths problem described
in [1].

The software is designed to run under UNIX (most flavors)
and requires the LEDA library [2].


-------------------------------------------------------------
Installation
-------------------------------------------------------------

To compile programs:

1. if you need, edit the files "Makefile" and "src/Makefile"
2. from this directory type "make"

The binaries will then all be found in the "bin" subdirectory.


-------------------------------------------------------------
Execution
-------------------------------------------------------------

If you want to reproduce the experiments described in [1], move to the
directory "scripts" and run the scripts 'exp_*'. 

Results of these experiments are stored in the directory
"results". We have computed the average of consecutive rows by the
same parameters (but different seeds) in order to compute the final
data shown in the paper graphs. The final data is stored in files have
postfix "_a".


-------------------------------------------------------------
Other information
-------------------------------------------------------------

- Type 'make clean' to remove all the binaries.


-------------------------------------------------------------
Index of files and directories
-------------------------------------------------------------

See ./list


-------------------------------------------------------------
Acknowledgements
-------------------------------------------------------------

We are grateful to B.V.Cherkassky, A.V.Goldberg and T.Radzik
whose experimental works [3] have inspired us in designing and
realizing the implementation setup, the documentation, and the
directory structure of this package.


-------------------------------------------------------------
Bibliography
-------------------------------------------------------------

[1] C.Demetrescu, D.Frigioni, A.Marchetti-Spaccamela and U.Nanni,
"An Experimental Study of Dynamic Shortest Paths Algorithms for
Digraphs with mixed Arc Weights", Technical Report TR-35-99
Dipartimento di Informatica e Sistemistica Universita' di Roma
"La Sapienza", 1999.

[2] http://www.mpi-sb.mpg.de/LEDA

[3] B.V.Cherkassky, A.V.Goldberg, and T.Radzik, "Shortest Paths
Algorithms: Theory and Experimental Evaluation," Math Programming,
Vol. 73, pages 129--174, 1996.
